name: Debug.Watch
comment:
Log the input and output of a function to the console.

@docs watch, watch2, watch3

values.name: watch
values.comment:
You can use it by putting it in front of a function youâ€™re trying to debug.

    import Debug.Watch as Debug

    addOne x =
        x + 1

    x =
        Debug.watch "add one" addOne 5

results in a console log of

    add one
        input: 5
       output: 6

values.name: watch2
values.comment: Same as `watch, but for a function with 2 arguments.
values.type: String -> (a -> b -> c) -> a -> b -> c

values.name: watch3
values.type: String -> (a -> b -> c -> d) -> a -> b -> c -> d
